article.headline: Fla Atlantic 93, East Tenn. St. 87
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Rodney Webb scored 30 points to lead Florida Atlantic to a 93-87 victory over East Tennessee State Thursday. The 42-29 lead Florida Atlantic (12-12, 11-6) took in the first half was too much for ETSU (15-10, 12-6) to overcome, despite outscoring Florida Atlantic 58-51 in the second half. In addition to Webb, DeAndre Rice scored 23 points for Florida Atlantic, with another 12 by Paul Graham. Courtney Pigram scored 22 points for ETSU, Dillion Sneed scored 20, Tim Smith scored 17 and Travis Strong scored 11. Along with his contribution to the team's score, Sneed grabbed 15 rebounds.
